extends ./layout.pug

block header
  .container.mt-5
      .row
        .col
          h1 Star Stuff API
block main
  .container.mb-5
    .row
      .col
        p An API containing information on celestial objects, including getting the altitude and azimuth of an object base on your datetime and location.
        h2.mb-3 Celestial Object Model
        h3 Properties
        table.mb-5
          thead
            tr
              th Property
              th Type
              th Description
              th Notes
          tbody
            tr
              td name
              td string
              td
                | The name of the celestial object
                em e.g. M1
              td required.
            tr
              td commonName
              td string
              td
                | The common name of the celestial object. For Messier objects this includes the NGC number.
                em e.g. The Crab Nebula
              td
            tr
              td type
              td string
              td
                | The type of the celestial object
                em e.g. Supernova Remnant
              td
            tr
              td rightAscension
              td string
              td
                | The right ascension of the celestial object
                em e.g. 5h 34.5m
              td
            tr
              td declination
              td string
              td
                | The declination of the celestial object
                em e.g. +22d 01m
              td
            tr
              td apparentMagnitude
              td string
              td
                | The apparent magnitude of the celestial object
                em e.g. 8.4
              td
            tr
              td constellation
              td string
              td
                | The constellation that the celestial object is closest to or in.
                em e.g. Taurus
              td
            tr
              td slug
              td string
              td
                | The url friendly version of the name.
                em e.g. m1
              td Auto-generated on creation.
            tr
              td recordCreated
              td string
              td
                | The datetime when the record was created.
                em e.g. m1
              td Auto-generated on creation.
        h3#methods.mb-3 Methods
        h4#getaltaz getAltAz
        p
          | Calculates the altitude and azimuth of the celestial body based on the users date, latitude, and longitude.
        h5#return-type Return Type
        pre.

        h5#parameters Parameters
        ul
          li
            | date: The date in local ISO format
            em e.g. 2021-02-09T23:00:00
          li
            | lat: The latitude in degree decimals
            em e.g. 42.36
          li
            | lon: The longitude in degree decimals
            em e.g. -71.05
        h2#endpoints Endpoints
        p.mb-4
          | Host URL is&nbsp;
          a(href='https://star-stuff.herokuapp.com/') https://star-stuff.herokuapp.com/
        h3#get-all-celestial-objects Get All Celestial Objects
        p.mb-0
          code GET /star-stuff/v1/celestials
        p Returns an array of all the celestial objects in the API.
        h3#get-one-celestial-object.mt-4 Get One Celestial Object
        p.mb-0
          code GET /star-stuff/v1/celestial/&lt;name&gt;
        p Returns one celestial object based on the provided name.
        h3#get-celestial-object-alt-az.mt-4 Get Celestial Object Alt/Az
        p.mb-0
          code GET /star-stuff/v1/celestial/&lt;name&gt;/altaz?date=&lt;date&gt;&amp;lat=&lt;lat&gt;&amp;lon=&lt;lon&gt;
        p
          | Returns the altitude and azimuth of the celestial object based on the given date, latitude, and longitude.
        h3#edit-celestial-object.mt-4 Edit Celestial Object
        p.mb-0
          code PATCH /star-stuff/v1/celestial/&lt;name&gt;
        p
          | Edits a celestial object. The properties and their new valeus should be included in the request body. Requires write access.
        h3#create-celestial-object.mt-4 Create Celestial Object
        p.mb-0
          code POST /star-stuff/v1/new-celestial
        p
          | Creates a new celestial object. The proeprties of the object should be included in the request body. Requires write access.
        h3#delete-celestial-object.mt-4 Delete Celestial Object
        p.mb-0
          code DELETE /star-stuff/v1/celestial/&lt;name&gt;
        p Deletes a celestial object. Requires write access.
        h2#contributing.mt-5 Contributing
        p
          | If you would like to add to the API database, you can request write access by emailing me at&nbsp;
          a(href="mailto:mail@ashpjohns.com") mail@ashpjohns.com
          | .
        p
          | If you would like to contribute to the codebase, go ahead and create issues or even put up a pull request.
